"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-07-team-gb-star-disrespected-fellow-olympian-explains-nasty-feud-21376127\", \"text\": \"Team GB star Josh Kerr believes he was 'disrespected' by a fellow Olympian as he explained his nasty feud with fierce 1500m rival Jakob Ingebrigtsen.  Kerr clinched a silver medal for Great Britain in the 1500m final at theOlympic GamesinParison Tuesday,missing out on goldto Team USA's Cole Hocker.  Norwegian runner Ingebrigtsen failed to make the podium - finishing fourth behind American Yared Nuguse - who walked away with the bronze medal.  After the final, Kerr, who ran the race in a British-record time of 3:27.79, was asked about Ingebrigtsen andexplained how the rivalry intensifiedin Budapest last year.  'Over the years there has been a bit of back and forth,' Kerr toldEurosportwhen asked to 'spill the tea' about his bitter feud with Ingebrigtsen.  'I felt a little bit disrespected last year after my first world title (at the 2023 World Championships in Budapest, Hungary).  'There is something about someone saying they are not 100 per cent when you go out and get your first world title that makes it sting a bit.  'I want everyone to be at their best and I want to beat everyone at their best. That's where it started for me, and I just started being honest with the questions.  'I was asked and instead of giving everyone the benefit of the doubt, I was being myself without much filter.  'I think that annoyed some people and turned some heads. Running and athletics is a gentleman's sport so there is not a lot of that, but it is what it is.'  Josh Kerr spills the tea on his rivalry with Jakob Ingebrigtsen \\u00e2\\u0098\\u0095\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0091\\u0080#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/3Bq6C5JBn5  Ingebrigtsen, who said he could beat Kerr blindfolded earlier this year, posted about the Briton on Instagram after Tuesday night's race at the Stade de France.  'Well, I guess he did show up after all\\u2026!' Ingebrigtsen said about Kerr on his social media account.  'Hocker and Nuguse as well\\u2026 My team always say that 'because you have a big mouth and is the one to beat, you have everything to lose in competitions'.  Jakob Ingebrigtsen aimed a massive dig at Josh Kerr in February.  'It is not certain that [Kerr] runs any better now than last year at the same time; he did not run two miles then,' Ingebrigtsen toldTV2in Norway.  'I would have beaten him in that race, blindfolded\\u2026 But it's good that people run better than they have done before.'  'Today, Cole Hocker, Yared Nuguse and Josh Kerr outsmarted me.  'They were 'the best guys' when it really mattered. And I want to congratulate them all on a great performance! Of course, I am disappointed!  'Thank you also to all my competitors for putting on a great show today. Congratulations to the guys bringing home the medals!'  ArrowMORE:Best new mobile games on iOS and Android - August 2024 round-up  ArrowMORE:India wrestler Vinesh Phogat disqualified from Olympic final for being 100g overweight  ArrowMORE:WWE legend sends message to record-breaking Olympic wrestler after historic gold  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"